            <biogHist>
                <p>Lachlan (Lachlane or Lachlin) MacDonald was born the son of Archy MacDonald,
                    fisherman, and Marion MacDonald n√©e MacLellan. In 1860 he married Christian or
                    Christine McLeod and seems to have worked as a cottar and shepherd throughout
                    his life, although by the time of the 1891 census he is listed as a weaver. The
                    couple had at least three children; at the time of the 1901 census they were
                    living with two of their children and a number of grand-children. On 13 March
                    1866 he was visited by Alexander Carmichael in Grimsay. </p>
                <p>He died of influenza in Grimsay, North Uist in 1919, a widower, and his daughter
                    Marion MacKenzie witnessed the certificate.</p>
